By Mohammad Tijjani Kaduna – The Nigerian Defence Academy (NDA) on Thursday said it had extended the application deadline for 71 Regular Course by two weeks. The Academy’s Public Relations Officer, Major Abdullahi Abubakar, made the disclosure in a statement issued in Kaduna. According to Abubakar, the NDA wishes to inform all applicants that the 71 Regular Course ‘Application Deadline’ has been extended by two weeks. “The application will now close on Thursday, March 28, 2019,’’ he said. (NAN)